title: 8 houses built in impossible places
description: Architecture can flirt with nature in expressive yet subtle ways. The idea in architecture is often to harmonize, not dominate, the landscapes. This can prove a challenge, however, when faced with steep slopes, cliff faces and mountainsides.

title: What happened when Democrats played a clip of Graham in 1999
description: Impeachment manager Rep. Jerry Nadler (D) plays a clip of Sen. Lindsey Graham (R-SC) from 1999 during the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump.

title: Frank Sinatra's gold-seated toilets up for auction
description: Frank Sinatra fans are set to scoop up furnishings, including gold-seated toilets, from an auction of contents belonging the late crooner's suite at the Golden Nugget Casino in Atlantic City, New Jersey.

title: Sharks that can walk discovered near Australia
description: Scientists discovered four new species off walking sharks near the northern coast of Australia.

title: Destinations have vowed to fight back against overtourism for 2020
description: If 2018 was the year of overtourism, 2019 was the year destinations fought back. Or, rather, vowed to do so. So how will 2020 shape up?

title: What Israel's Holocaust memorial can teach us today
description: Ahead of the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz concentration camp, CNN's Sara Sidner tours Yad Vashem, Israel's national Holocaust remembrance site.

title: How you can prevent contracting the virus
description: CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta looks at what you need to know about the Wuhan virus and coronaviruses like MERS and SARS in general, from what they are to how you can treat them.
